(standardizing,standardized,standardizes) BRIT also  standardise 

1. V-T To standardize things means to change them so that they all have the same features. 使标准化 

例： There is a drive both to standardize components and to reduce the number of models. 有一种使零部件标准化并减少型号数量的需求。 

2. standardization N-UNCOUNT 标准化 

例： ...the standardization of working hours. …工作时间的标准化。

